        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 1:04AM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 104 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Belgreen, or 12 miles east of Tishomingo State
Park, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Phil Campbell, Belgreen, Vina, Hodges, Cedar Creek Reservoir, Atwood,
Srygley Church, Duketon, Rockwood, and Halltown.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
